-- England Reaches 103-2 at Lunch on Day 1 of Opening Test Against Pakistan
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-07-29T12:11:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/england-reaches-103-2-at-lunch-on-day-1-of-opening-test-against-pakistan.html

          
          
             England reached 103-2 at lunch on
the opening day of the first cricket Test against Pakistan at
Trent Bridge in Nottingham.  
 Jonathan Trott has 35 runs for England, which won the toss
and elected to bat first. Captain Andrew Strauss scored 45
before being caught by Kamal Akmal off Mohammad Aamer, who is
2-28.  
 Kevin Pietersen is on 1 for England, while Alastair Cook
scored 8.  
          
          


  


        